{
  "stem": "4361.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And after that, you went to university, which was, you know, the second-- as I said, equivalent of two years college by that time.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But it was very easy, I must say.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we took a deep breath, Susie and I.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we are going to go back to Sighet.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we got into the last train, I believe, pulling out from Kolozsvar to Sighet.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And it kept stopping quite often because other trains were coming.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I remember those other trains for which this train had to stop were coming from the east and were full of wounded soldiers, Wehrmacht.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "That was the first time because this is now 1944.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Stalingrad had fallen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Leningrad, had been-- the siege had been broken.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "They were already rolling down, down, down, I mean, from east to west.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And the trains were full of wounded soldiers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just to get to home to be with my family, to be with my family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Couldn't, couldn't contemplate the future.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was just moment to moment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I should be home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I should be with my family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "By that time, both my brothers had been conscripted in what was called the Auxiliary Hungarian Army.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It wasn't really a Hungarian Army.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a slave labor brigade into which the Jewish boys were conscripted.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They wore a yellow band.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had no uniform, no weapons.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And their job was to go-- they were sent with the Hungarian army to help the Germans on the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And their job was tantamount to being minesweepers because they were sent ahead to clear the fields and so forth.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My older brother Moshe, who by that time was already married, and his little boy was born while he was in Russia, eventually, eventually came back in December 1943 with terrible news.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
